<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center; font-size:larger; background-color:#ed8; color:#000;" class="fn summary">Ryūichi Sakamoto</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="padding: 0px; padding-top: 2px; text-align:center; font-size:100%;" class=""><a href="/wiki/File:RyuichiSakamotoJI4.jpg" class="image" title="RyuichiSakamotoJI4.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/RyuichiSakamotoJI4.jpg/180px-RyuichiSakamotoJI4.jpg" width="180" height="121" border="0" /></a><br />
<small>Ryūichi Sakamoto June 2007</small></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Born</th>
<td>January 17, 1952 <span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1952-01-17</span>)</span> <span class="noprint">(age&#160;57)</span><br />
<a href="/wiki/Tokyo,_Japan" title="Tokyo, Japan" class="mw-redirect">Tokyo, Japan</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th><span style="white-space:nowrap;">Spouse(s)</span></th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Akiko_Yano" title="Akiko Yano">Akiko Yano</a> (1955-) (divorced in 2006)</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Ryūichi Sakamoto</b> (<a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E5%9D%82" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:坂">坂</a><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E6%9C%AC" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:本">本</a> <a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E9%BE%8D" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:龍">龍</a><a href="http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E4%B8%80" class="extiw" title="wiktionary:一">一</a> <i>Sakamoto Ryūichi</i>, born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1952-01-17"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="01-17"><a href="/wiki/January_17" title="January 17">January 17</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1952" title="1952">1952</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/Nakano" title="Nakano">Nakano</a>, <a href="/wiki/Tokyo" title="Tokyo">Tokyo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japan</a>) is an <a href="/wiki/Academy_Awards" title="Academy Awards" class="mw-redirect">Academy Award</a>-winning, <a href="/wiki/Grammy" title="Grammy" class="mw-redirect">Grammy</a>-winning, <a href="/wiki/Golden_Globe" title="Golden Globe" class="mw-redirect">Golden Globe</a>-winning <a href="/wiki/Japan" title="Japan">Japanese</a> <a href="/wiki/Musician" title="Musician">musician</a>, <a href="/wiki/Composer" title="Composer">composer</a>, <a href="/wiki/Record_producer" title="Record producer">producer</a> and <a href="/wiki/Actor" title="Actor">actor</a>, based in <a href="/wiki/New_York" title="New York">New York</a> and <a href="/wiki/Tokyo" title="Tokyo">Tokyo</a>.</p>
<p>His 1999 musical composition "Energy Flow" is the first number-one <a href="/wiki/Instrumental" title="Instrumental">instrumental</a> single in the Japan's <a href="/wiki/Oricon" title="Oricon">Oricon</a> charts history.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> He was ranked at number 59 in a list of the top 100 most influential musicians compiled by <a href="/wiki/HMV" title="HMV" class="mw-redirect">HMV</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
